; Regression test for issue #1634: Metadata/Note contents can't include
; a ledger formatted date (BZ#562)
;
; Bug 1: Querying tags whose values contain slashes (e.g. dates like
; 2011/08/30) failed because the query predicate serializer wrapped mask
; values in /.../ without escaping internal slashes, causing the
; expression parser to misinterpret them as regex delimiters.
;
; Bug 2: Typed metadata (Key:: Value) with a bare date like 2024/03/15
; was evaluated as arithmetic (2024 / 3 / 15 = 44.977...) instead of
; being recognized as a date literal.

2014/05/01 * Business Trip
    ; trip: 2011/08/30 Corona
    Expenses:Travel    $500.00
    Assets:Cash

2024/01/01 Invoice
    ; Due:: 2024/03/15
    Expenses:Food    $10.00
    Assets:Cash

; Bug 1: tag query with slashes in value should match correctly
test reg tag trip="2011/08/30 Corona"
14-May-01 Business Trip         Expenses:Travel             $500.00      $500.00
                                Assets:Cash                $-500.00            0
end test

; Bug 2: typed metadata date should be stored as a date, not arithmetic
test reg --limit 'account =~ /Food/' --format '%(tag("Due"))\n'
2024/03/15
end test
